  "identifier": "mappestRisk",
  "description": "There are three different modules: (1) model fitting & selection using a set of the most commonly used equations describing developmental responses to temperature helped by already existing R packages using equation helpers and parameters from 'devRate' (Rebaudo et al. 2018, <doi:10.1111/2041-210X.12935>) 'rTPC' and nonlinear regression model functions from 'nls.multstart' (Padfield et al. 2021, <doi:10.1111/2041-210X.13585>), with visualization of model predictions to guide ecological criteria for model selection; (2) calculation of suitability thermal limits, which consist on a temperature interval delimiting the optimal performance zone or suitability; and (3) climatic data extraction & visualization inspired on previous research (Taylor et al. 2019, <doi:10.1111/1365-2664.13455>), with either exportable rasters, static map images or html, interactive maps.",
  "name": "mappestRisk: Create Maps Forecasting Risk of Pest Occurrence",
